org.openbel.framework.common.model
Class Term

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.common.model.Term
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<Parameter>, BELObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
EquivalentTerm
public class Term
extends Object
implements BELObject, Iterable<Parameter>

BEL terms represent biological entities.

They contain a number of terms and parameters. Terms are parameter-iterable: 

 
 for (final Parameter parameter : term) {
     // ...
 }

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

getNumberOfArguments

public int getNumberOfArguments()
Returns the number of function arguments.

The arguments to a term's function can either be a parameter or another term (considered an inner term). This means the number_of_arguments is equal to the (number_of_parameters + number_of_terms). I.e., 

 
 getNumberOfArguments() == (getNumberOfParameters() + getNumberOfTerms())

Returns:
int
See Also:
getNumberOfParameters(), getNumberOfTerms()

getNumberOfParameters

public int getNumberOfParameters()
Returns the number of parameters.

The arguments to a term's function can either be a parameter or another term (considered an inner term). This means the number_of_parameters is equal to the (number_of_arguments - number_of_terms). I.e., 

 
 getNumberOfParameters() == (getNumberOfArguments() - getNumberOfTerms())

Returns:
int
See Also:
getNumberOfArguments(), getNumberOfTerms()

getNumberOfTerms

public int getNumberOfTerms()
Returns the number of terms.

The arguments to a term's function can either be a parameter or another term (considered an inner term). This means the number_of_terms is equal to the (number_of_arguments - number_of_parameters). I.e., 

 
 getNumberOfTerms() == (getNumberOfArguments() - getNumberOfParameters())

Returns:
int
See Also:
getNumberOfArguments(), getNumberOfParameters()

getFunctionArguments

public List<BELObject> getFunctionArguments()
Returns the term's arguments, in order, to its associated function.

The term's parameters and nested terms compose the arguments to its associated BEL function. This method encapsulates the ordering of these arguments for the term's function.

Returns:
List of BEL objects, which may be null, in order for its associated function

getAllParametersLeftToRight

public List<Parameter> getAllParametersLeftToRight()
Returns all of this term's Parameter objects, in a left to right sequence, contained within both the outer and inner terms.

Parameters are found in a recursive depth-first search using the implementation in findParameters(List, Term).

Returns:
List of all Parameter objects for this term, which can be empty but will not be null

findParameters

protected void findParameters(List<Parameter> parms,
                              Term trm)
Find all parameters in term in a left-to-right, depth-first fashion. The term's function arguments are read in order and the following rules apply:
  • If the function argument is a parameter:
    • Add it to the parameter list (ps).
  • If the function argument is a term:
    • Recurse into findParameters(List, Term) for the nested term.

The results are captured in the params List.

Parameters:
params - List of Parameter, the list of parameters found from the top-level term so far
